obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (28744)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28744&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Bank for`
  line `Agriculture and Rural Development Act, 1981.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and`
  line `any reference in any provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st May, 1982, vide notification No. S.O. 278(E), dated 21st April, 1982 (except sections 3, 16 and 18), see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line `12th July, 1982, vide notification No. S.O. 484(E), dated 6th July, 1982 (in respect sections 3, 16 and 18), see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (28745)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28745&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "agriculture" includes horticulture, animal husbandry, forestry, dairy and poultry farming,`
  line `pisciculture, and other allied activities, whether or not undertaken jointly with agriculture and the`
  line `expression "agricultural operations" shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "pisciculture" includes the development of`
  line `fisheries, both inland and marine, catching of fish and all activities connected therewith or incidental`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(b) "Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation" means the Corporation established`
  line `under section 3 of the Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation Act, 1963 (10 of 1963),`
  line `and renamed under section 3A of that Act as the Agricultural Refinance and Development`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(c) "Board" means the Board of Directors of the National Bank;`
  line
  line `(d) "central co-operative bank" means the principal co-operative society in a district in a State,`
  line `the primary object of which is the financing of other co-operative societies in that district:`
  line
  line `Provided that in addition to such principal society in a district, or where there is no such principal`
  line `society in a district, the State Government may declare any one or more co-operative societies`
  line `carrying on the business of financing other co-operative societies in that district to be also or to be a`
  line `central co-operative bank or central co-operative banks within the meaning of this definition;`
  line
  line `(e) "Chairman" means the Chairman ^1*** appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) "co-operative society" means a society registered, or deemed to be registered, under the`
  line `Co-operative Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912) or any other law relating to co-operative societies for`
  line `the time being in force in any State;`
  line
  line `(g) "crops" includes products of agricultural operations;`
  line
  line `(h) "director" means a director appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(j) "Managing Director" means the Managing Director appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `(k) "marketing of crops" includes the processing of crops prior to marketing by any agricultural`
  line `producers or any organisation of such producers;`
  line
  line `^3[(ka) "micro enterprise", "small enterprise" and "medium enterprise", shall have the same`
  line `meanings as are respectively assigned to them in the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises`
  line `Development Act, 2006 (27 of 2006)];`
  line
  line `(l) "National Bank" means the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development established`
  line `under section 3;`
  line
  line `(m) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(n) "primary rural credit society" means a co-operative society, by whatever name called,--`
  line
  line `(1) which has as its object or business the provision of financial accommodation to its`
  line `members for agriculture or agricultural operations or for the marketing of crops, or for rural`
  line `development; and`
  line
  line `(2) the bye-laws of which do not permit admission of any other co-operative society as`
  line `member:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-clause shall not apply to the admission, as a member, of a co-operative`
  line `society, which is a State co-operative bank or a central co-operative bank by reason of such bank`
  line `subscribing to the share capital of the co-operative society out of funds provided by the State`
  line `Government for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(o) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "regional rural bank" means a regional rural bank established under section 3 of the Regional`
  line `Rural Banks Act, 1976 (21 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(q) "rural development" means development of rural areas through any activities conducive to`
  line `such development.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(a) activities conducive to development of rural areas include activities relating to production`
  line `of goods or provision of services in rural areas and activities for the promotion of cottage and`
  line `village industries, ^4[micro-enterprises, small enterprises and medium enterprises, handicrafts,`
  line `handlooms] and other rural crafts;`
  line
  line `(b) "rural area" means the area comprised in any village and includes the area comprised in`
  line `any town, the population of which does not exceed ten thousand or such other figure as the`
  line `Reserve Bank may specify from time to time;`
  line
  line `(r) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(s) "scheduled bank" means a bank for the time being included in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(u) "State co-operative bank" means the principal co- operative society in a State, the primary`
  line `object of which is the financing of other co-operative societies in the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that in addition to such principal society in a State, or where there is no such principal`
  line `society in a State, the State Government may declare any one or more co-operative societies carrying`
  line `on business in that State to be also or to be a State co-operative bank or State co-operative banks`
  line `within the meaning of this definition;`
  line
  line `(v) "State land development bank" means the co-operative society which is the principal land`
  line `development bank (by whatever name called) in a State and which has as its primary object the`
  line `providing of long-term finance for agricultural development:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in addition to such principal land development bank in a State, or where there is no`
  line `such bank in a State, the State Government may declare any co-operative society carrying on business`
  line `in that State and authorised by the bye-laws of such co-operative society to provide long-term finance`
  line `for agricultural development to be also or to be a State land development bank within the meaning of`
  line `this definition;`
  line
  line `(w) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act;`
  line
  line `(x) words and expressions used herein and not defined either in this Act or in the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), but defined in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), shall have`
  line `the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "of the Board" omitted by Act 55 of 2000, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (i) omitted by Act 7 of 2018, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "industry in the tiny and decentralised sector and small-scale industry and handicrafts"`
  line `(w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (t) omitted by Act 7 of 2018, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (28746)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "Bombay" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28746&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established for the purposes of this Act, a bank to be known as the`
  line `National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bank shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property`
  line `and to contract, and may by that name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the National Bank shall be at ^1[Mumbai] or at such other place as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) The National Bank may establish offices, branches or agencies at any place in India, and with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government and in consultation with the Reserve Bank, at any place`
  line `outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (28747)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Capital.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28747&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The capital of the National Bank shall be one hundred crores of rupees:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, increase the said capital up to thirty`
  line `thousand crore rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank and by`
  line `notification, further increase the said capital to such amount as it may deem necessary from time to time].`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The capital of the National Bank which has been subscribed to by the Reserve Bank valued at`
  line `twenty crore rupees as on the date immediately preceding the commencement of the National Bank for`
  line `Agriculture and Rural Development (Amendment) Act, 2018 shall, on such commencement, stand`
  line `transferred to, and vested in, the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Bank may issue capital to such institutions and persons in such manner as`
  line `may be notified by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the combined shareholding of the Central Government and the Reserve Bank`
  line `shall not at any time be less than fifty-one per cent. of the total subscribed capital.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall give to the Reserve Bank an amount equal to the face value of the`
  line `subscribed capital, valued at twenty crores of rupees, referred to in sub-section (2), in cash, for transfer to,`
  line `and vesting in the Central Government of the capital of the National Bank which has been so subscribed`
  line `to by the said Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso subs by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by Act 7 of 2018, s. 5, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (28748)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Management.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 43 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28748&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs and`
  line `business of the National Bank shall vest in a Board of Directors, which shall exercise all powers and do`
  line `all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board in discharging its functions, shall act on business`
  line `principles with due regard to public interest.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) and save as otherwise provided in the regulations`
  line `made under this Act, the Managing Director shall also have powers of general superintendence, direction`
  line `and management of the affairs and business of the National Bank and may also exercise all powers and do`
  line `all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the National Bank:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that during the period of any casual vacancy of the nature referred to in section 11 in the`
  line `office of the Managing Director, the Chairman may also exercise the powers and discharge the functions`
  line `of the Managing Director until the person appointed by the Central Government under section 11 to act as`
  line `Managing Director enters upon his office.]`
  line
  line `(4) Any whole-time director appointed under sub-section (3) of section 6 shall assist the Managing`
  line `Director in the discharge of his functions under sub-section (3) and perform such duties as the Board may`
  line `entrust or delegate to him.`
  line
  line `(5) In the discharge of his powers and functions under sub-section (3), the Managing Director shall`
  line `follow such directions as the Chairman may give.`
  line
  line `(6) In the discharge of its functions under this Act, the National Bank shall be guided by such`
  line `directions in matters of policy involving public interest as the Central Government, in consultation with`
  line `the Reserve Bank, or the Reserve Bank, may give in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (28749)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Board of Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28749&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Board of Directors of the National Bank shall consist of the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) three directors from amongst experts in rural economics, rural development, village and`
  line `cottage industries, ^2[micro-enterprises, small-scale industries] or persons having experience in the working of co-operative`
  line `banks, regional rural banks or commercial banks or any other matter the special knowledge or`
  line `professional experience in which is considered by the Central Government as useful to the National`
  line Bank;
  line
  line `(c) three directors from out of the directors of the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(d) three directors from amongst the officials of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) four directors from amongst the officials of the State Governments;`
  line
  line `(f) such number of directors elected in the prescribed manner, by shareholders other than the`
  line `Reserve Bank, the Central Government and other institutions owned or controlled by the Central`
  line `Government whose names are entered on the register of shareholders of the National Bank ninety days before the date of the meeting in which such election takes place on the following basis,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where the total amount of equit..................................................`
  line `share capital issued to such shareholders is ten per cent. or less of the`
  line `total issued equity capital`
  line `two directors;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the total amount of equity................................................`
  line `share capital issued to such shareholders is more than ten per cent.`
  line `but less than twenty-five per cent. of the total issued equity capital`
  line `three directors;`
  line and
  line
  line `(iii) where the total equity share capital.........................................`
  line `issued to such shareholders is twenty-five per cent. or more of the`
  line `total issued equity capital:`
  line `four directors:`
  line
  line `Provided that until the assumption of charge by the elected directors under this clause, the`
  line `Central Government may at any time nominate such number of directors not exceeding four from`
  line `amongst persons having special knowledge of, and professional experience in, agricultural`
  line `science, technology, economics, banking, co-operatives, law, rural finance, investment,`
  line `accountancy, marketing or any other matter, the special knowledge of, and professional`
  line `experience in, which would, in the opinion of the Central Government, be useful to the National`
  line `Bank for carrying out its functions; and`
  line
  line `(g) a Managing Director.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman and other directors, excluding the directors referred to in clause (f), shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government in consultation with the Reserve Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such consultation shall be necessary in the case of directors appointed under clause`
  line `(d) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Central Government is satisfied, in consultation with the Reserve Bank,`
  line `^3*** that it is`
  line `necessary so to do, it may appoint one or more whole-time directors with such designations as may be`
  line `deemed appropriate by that Government and any whole-time director so appointed shall also be a member`
  line `of the Board.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 5, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 6, for "small-scale industries" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The words "and the Board" omitted by Act 81 of 1985, s. 17(w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
  line
  line `4. The proviso omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (28750)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Term of office of Chairman and other directors, retirement and payment of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28750&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairman shall hold office for such term not exceeding five years and shall receive such salary and`
  line `allowances as the Central Government may, at the time of appointment, specify ^1[and shall be eligible for`
  line `reappointment]:`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have the`
  line `right to terminate the term of office of the Chairman at any time before the expiry of the term specified`
  line `under that sub-section by giving him a notice of not less than three months in writing or three months`
  line `salary and allowances in lieu of such notice.]`
  line
  line `^4[(1B) In the case of a vacancy in the office of the Chairman, the Managing Director shall perform the`
  line `functions and duties of the Chairman during such vacancy.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (5), a director appointed under clause (b) or`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 6, shall hold office for such term, not exceeding three years, as the`
  line `Central Government may specify in this behalf, ^6*** and shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, remove the Chairman`
  line `at any time before the expiry of his term of office after giving him a reasonable opportunity of showing`
  line `cause against the proposed removal.`
  line
  line `^7[(4) The Chairman and any other director, who is not an officer of the Central Government or a State`
  line `State Government or an officer of the Reserve Bank or any body or corporation established by or under`
  line `any Central Act or any State Act and owned or controlled by such Government, shall be paid such fees`
  line `and allowances as may be prescribed for attending the meetings of the Board or of any of its committees`
  line `and for attending to any other work of the National Bank.]`
  line
  line `^8[(5) The directors appointed under clauses (b) to (f) of sub-section (1) of section 6 shall hold office`
  line `during the pleasure of the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 55 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 81 of 1985, s.18 (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (1-5-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 45, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `6. The words "and thereafter until his successor enters upon his office" omitted by Act 55 of 2000, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 6, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 45 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (28751)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Term of office of Managing Director and whole-time directors, conditions of service, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 55 of 2000, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28751&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Managing Director and any whole-time director appointed under sub-section (3) of section 6`
  line shall,--
  line
  line `(a) hold office for such term not exceeding five years as the Central Government may, at the time`
  line `of appointment, specify ^1[and shall be eligible for reappointment];`
  line
  line `(b) receive such salary and allowances and be governed by such terms and conditions of service`
  line `as the Board may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and in consultation with the`
  line `Reserve Bank, determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Managing Director and any such whole-time director appointed to the first`
  line `Board shall receive such salary and allowances and be governed by such terms and conditions of`
  line `service as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, determine.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, remove the Managing`
  line `Director or any whole-time director appointed under sub-section (3) of section 6 at any time before the`
  line `expiry of his term of office, after giving him a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the`
  line `proposed removal.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Central Government`
  line `shall have the right to terminate the term of office of the Managing Director or of any whole-time director`
  line `appointed under sub-section (3) of section 6 at any time before the expiry of the term fixed under`
  line `sub-section (1) by giving him notice of not less than three months in writing or three months' salary and`
  line `allowances in lieu of such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall, before terminating the term of office of the Managing`
  line `Director or any whole-time director appointed under sub-section (3) of section 6, consult the Reserve`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (28752)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28752&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be a director who--`
  line
  line `(a) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(b) is or has been convicted of any offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or at any time has been, adjudicated insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts or has`
  line `compounded with his creditors.`
  line
  line `(2) The appointment as director of any person who is a Member of Parliament or the Legislature of`
  line `any State shall, unless within two months of the date of his appointment he ceases to be such member, be`
  line `void on the expiry of the said period of two months and if any director is elected or nominated as a`
  line `Member of Parliament or of any State Legislature he shall cease to be a director as from the date of such`
  line `election or nomination, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (28753)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Vacation and resignation of office by directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28753&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a director--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 9; or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the Board for more than three consecutive meetings thereof,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(2) Any director may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the Central Government,`
  line `and on his resignation being accepted by the Central Government or if his resignation is not sooner`
  line `accepted, on the expiry of three months from the receipt thereof by the Central Government, he shall be`
  line `deemed to have vacated his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (28754)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Casual vacancy in the office of Managing Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28754&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `If the Managing Director is by infirmity`
  line `or otherwise rendered incapable of carrying out his duties or is absent on leave or otherwise, in`
  line `circumstances not involving the vacation of his appointment, the Central Government may, after`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank and the Board, appoint another person to act in his place as Managing`
  line `Director during his absence.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (28755)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. ns. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28755&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such`
  line `rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the Board, or, if for any reason he is unable to attend any meeting, ^1[the`
  line `Managing Director and in the absence of both, the Chairman and the Managing Director] any other`
  line `director nominated by the Chairman in this behalf, and in the absence of such nomination, any other`
  line `director elected by the directors present at the meeting, shall preside at the meeting of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `votes of the directors present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman, or, in his`
  line `absence, the person presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (28756)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Committees of National Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28756&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may constitute an Executive Committee`
  line `consisting of such number of directors as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall discharge such functions as may be prescribed or may be`
  line `delegated to it by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may constitute such other committees, whether consisting wholly of directors or`
  line `wholly of other persons or partly of directors and partly of other persons as it thinks fit and for such`
  line `purposes as it may decide and every committee so constituted shall discharge such functions as may be`
  line `delegated to it by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Executive Committee shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The times and places at which any committee constituted under sub-section (3) shall meet, the`
  line `rules of procedure which such committee shall observe in regard to the transaction of business at its`
  line `meetings, and the fees and allowances which may be paid to the members of such committee for attending`
  line `the meetings of the committee and for attending to any other work of the National Bank shall be such as`
  line `may be specified by that Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (28757)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28757&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[The Board may] constitute an Advisory Council consisting of such`
  line `number of directors and such other persons who, in the opinion of the Board, have special knowledge of`
  line `agriculture, agricultural credit, co-operation and rural economics, ^2[micro-enterprises, small-scale industries,] village and`
  line `cottage industries and handicrafts and other rural crafts or have special knowledge and appreciation of the`
  line `country's overall developmental policies and in particular overall monetary and credit policies, which is`
  line `considered by the Board as useful to the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Council shall advise the National Bank in such matters as may be referred to the`
  line `Advisory Council by the National Bank and may discharge such other functions as may be entrusted or`
  line `delegated to the Advisory Council by the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) A member of the Advisory Council shall hold office for such term not exceeding five years as the`
  line `National Bank may fix, and receive such fees and allowances as may be prescribed for attending the`
  line `meetings of the Advisory Council and for attending to any other work of the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) The Advisory Council shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to transaction of business at its meetings as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by 55 of 2000, s. 9, for The Board shall (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 7, for "small-scale industries" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (28758)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Member of Board or Committee thereof not to participate in meetings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28758&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line A
  line `director of the Board or a member of a Committee, who has any direct or indirect pecuniary interest in`
  line `any matter coming up for consideration at a meeting of the Board or a Committee thereof, shall, as soon`
  line `as possible after relevant circumstances have come to his knowledge, disclose the nature of his interest at`
  line `such meeting, and the disclosure shall be recorded in the minutes of the Board, or the Committee, as the`
  line `case may be, and the director or member shall not take any part in any deliberation or decision of the`
  line `Board or the Committee with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (28759)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Transfer of assets and liabilities of Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28759&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) On such date as the Central Government, in consultation with the Reserve Bank may, by notification,`
  line `appoint, the entire undertaking of the Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation (hereafter in`
  line `this Chapter referred to as the "Corporation") including all business, property, assets and liabilities, rights,`
  line `interests, privileges and obligations of whatever nature, shall stand transferred to and vest in the National`
  line Bank.
  line
  line `(2) As compensation for the transfer of the undertaking of the Corporation to the National Bank under`
  line `sub-section (1), the National Bank shall within six months from the date appointed under that sub-section`
  line `(hereafter in this section referred to as the appointed date) pay to the shareholders of the Corporation a`
  line `sum equal to the total paid-up capital of the Corporation as on the date immediately preceding the`
  line `appointed date.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of compensation payable under sub-section (2) to the shareholders of the Corporation`
  line `shall be apportioned among the shareholders in proportion to their contributions to the paid-up capital of`
  line `the Corporation as on the date immediately preceding the appointed date.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "shareholders of the Corporation" means`
  line `shareholders of the Corporation whose names appear on the register of shareholders maintained under`
  line `section 8 of the Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation Act, 1963 (10 of 1963), on the date`
  line `immediately preceding the appointed date.`
  line
  line `(4) The National Bank shall also pay to the shareholders of the Corporation referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) an amount calculated at the rate at which the shares of the Corporation were guaranteed as`
  line `to the payment of minimum divided under section 6 of the Agricultural Refinance and Development`
  line `Corporation Act, 1963 (10 of 1963), for the period, if any, that has expired in the accounting year of the`
  line `Corporation before the appointed date and this amount the National Bank shall distribute to the`
  line `shareholders of the Corporation referred to in sub-section (2) in proportion to the shares held by such shareholders on the date immediately preceding the appointed date and at the rate at which such shares`
  line `were guaranteed as to the payment of minimum dividend.`
  line
  line `(5) All contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers of attorney, grants of legal representation and`
  line `other instruments of whatever nature subsisting or having effect immediately before the appointed date`
  line `and to which the Corporation is a party, or which are in favour of the Corporation, shall be of as full force`
  line `and effect against or in favour of the National Bank, as the case may be, and may be enforced or acted`
  line `upon as fully and effectually as if instead of the Corporation the National Bank had been a party thereto,`
  line `or as if they had been in favour of the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(6) If, immediately before the appointed date, any suit, appeal or other legal proceeding of whatever`
  line `nature, is pending, by or against the Corporation, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be in any`
  line `way prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer to the National Bank of the undertaking of the`
  line `Corporation, or of anything contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be`
  line `continued, prosecuted and enforced, by or against the National Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (28760)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Dissolution of the Corporation and repeal of Act 10 of 1963.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28760&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `On the date appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Corporation shall stand dissolved; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation Act, 1963, shall stand repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (28761)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Transfer of business from Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28761&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) On such date as the Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank, by notification, appoint, the assets and liabilities with the Reserve`
  line `Bank relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) the National Agricultural Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund established and maintained`
  line `under section 46A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); and`
  line
  line `(b) the National Agricultural Credit (Stabilisation) Fund established and maintained under section`
  line `46B of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934),`
  line
  line `shall stand transferred to the National Bank and form part of the National Rural Credit (Long Term`
  line `Operations) Fund referred to in section 42 and the National Rural Credit (Stabilisation) Fund referred to`
  line `in section 43, respectively.`
  line
  line `(2) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve`
  line `Bank, by notification, appoint, the loans and advances which the Reserve Bank has granted to State`
  line `co-operative banks and regional rural banks under section 17 [except sub-clause (a) of clause (4) of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), and which the Reserve Bank may specify by a general or`
  line `special order, shall, as far as may be, become and be deemed to be loans and advances granted by the`
  line `National Bank under section 21, and the National Bank shall repay to the Reserve Bank, the amount of`
  line `such loans and advances on such terms and conditions as the Central Government may specify, in`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) All rights, liabilities interests, privileges and obligations of whatever nature (including the rights`
  line `and obligations arising by way of purchase, sale and rediscount of any bills of exchange and promissory`
  line `notes) of the Reserve Bank in relation to any asset or liability referred to in sub-section (1) or any loan or`
  line `advance referred to in sub-section (2) shall stand transferred to and vest in the National Bank on the date`
  line `on which such asset or liability stands transferred to the National Bank under sub-section (1) or, as the`
  line `case may be, such loan or advance becomes under sub-section (2) a loan or advance granted by the`
  line `National Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) All contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers of attorney, grants of legal representation and`
  line `other instruments of whatever nature relating to any asset or liability referred to in sub-section (1) and`
  line `subsisting or having effect immediately before the date appointed under that sub-section or relating to any`
  line `loan or advance referred to in sub-section (2) and subsisting or having effect immediately before the date`
  line `appointed under that sub-section shall be of as full force and effect against, or in favour of, the National`
  line `Bank, as the case may be, and may be enforced or acted upon as fully and effectually as if instead of the`
  line `Reserve Bank, the National Bank had been a party thereto, or as if they had been in favour of the National`
  line Bank.
  line
  line `(5) If, immediately before the date appointed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may`
  line `be, any suit, appeal or other legal proceedings of whatever nature relating to any asset or liability referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) or any loan or advance referred to in sub-section (2) is pending, by or against the`
  line `Reserve Bank, the same shall not abate, be discontinued, or be in any way prejudicially affected by reason`
  line `of the transfer to the National Bank of such asset or liability under sub-section (1), or as the case may be,`
  line `such loan or advance becoming under sub-section (2) a loan or advance granted by the National Bank, or`
  line `of anything contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceedings may be continued, prosecuted`
  line `and enforced, by or against the National Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (28762)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Borrowings by the National Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28762&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank may, for the purpose of carrying out its`
  line `functions under this Act,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) issue and sell bonds, debentures and other financial instruments with or without guarantee of`
  line `the Central Government on such terms and conditions as may be approved by the Board;]`
  line
  line `^2[(b) borrow money from the Reserve Bank repayable on demand or otherwise on such terms and`
  line `conditions including the terms relating to security and purposes as may be specified by the Reserve`
  line Bank;
  line
  line `(c) borrow money from the Central Government and from any other authority or organisation or`
  line `institution approved by the Board, on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon;`
  line
  line `(d) accept from the Central Government, a State Government, a local authority, a State land`
  line `development bank, a State co-operative bank or a scheduled bank or any person or body, whether`
  line `incorporated or not, deposits repayable on such terms as the National Bank may, with the approval of`
  line `the Reserve Bank, fix; and`
  line
  line `(e) receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government or any other source.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 10, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 26-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for clauses (b) to (e) (w.e.f. 26-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (28763)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Borrowings in foreign currency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for section 20 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28763&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Borrowings in foreign currency.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999), or in any other law for the time being in force, relating to`
  line `foreign exchange, the National Bank may borrow, with the previous approval of the Central Government`
  line `and in consultation with the Reserve Bank, foreign currency from any bank or financial institution in`
  line `India or elsewhere, for granting loans and advances or for utilising such currency for any other purpose`
  line `specified under the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (28764)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Production and marketing credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28764&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Bank may provide by way of refinance,`
  line `loans and advances, repayable on demand or on the expiry of fixed periods not exceeding eighteen`
  line `months, ^1[to State co-operative banks, central co-operative banks], regional rural banks, or to any`
  line `financial institution or to any class of financial institutions, which are approved by the Reserve Bank in`
  line `this behalf, for financing--`
  line
  line `(i) agricultural operations or the marketing of crops, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the marketing and distribution of inputs necessary for agriculture or rural development, or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other activity for the promotion of or in the field of agriculture or rural development, or`
  line
  line `(iv) bona fide commercial or trade transactions, or`
  line
  line `(v) the production or marketing activities of artisans or of ^2[village and cottage industries, microenterprises, small enterprises and medium enterprises or of those engaged in the field of handicrafts,`
  line `handlooms] and other rural crafts. .`
  line
  line `(2) The National Bank may make loans and advances under sub-section (1) against the security of--`
  line
  line `(i) stocks, funds and securities other than immovable property, in which a trustee is authorised to`
  line `invest trust money by any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(ii) promissory notes supported by documents of title to goods, such documents having been`
  line `transferred, assigned or pledged to the borrowing institution as security for a loan or advance made`
  line `for any of the purposes specified in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Bank may, whenever it considers it necessary so to do, accept, in lieu`
  line `of the actual assignment of any such security in favour of the National Bank, a declaration in writing`
  line `from the borrowing institution,--`
  line
  line `(a) stating that it holds such documents such documents of title to goods as may be set out in`
  line `the declaration; and`
  line
  line `(b) containing such other particulars as may be required by the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the National Bank may in its discretion`
  line `grant a loan or advance--`
  line
  line `(a) ^3[to any State co-operative bank or central co-operative bank] if the loan or advance is fully`
  line `guaranteed for repayment of principal and interest by Government;`
  line
  line `(b) to any State co-operative bank which is a scheduled bank, if the loan or advance is secured`
  line `either by a bill of exchange or promissory note executed by the central co-operative bank and`
  line `assigned in favour of the State co-operative bank.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (2) and (3), the National Bank may also make`
  line `loans and advances repayable on demand or on the expiry of fixed periods not exceeding eighteen months`
  line `against promissory notes of a State co-operative bank or a regional rural bank or an institution approved`
  line `under sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the borrowing institution furnishes a declaration in writing, setting out the purpose for`
  line `which it has made loans and advances and such other particulars as may be required by the National`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 2003, s. 2, for "to State co-operative banks" (w.e.f. 19-9-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 8, for "small-scale industries, industries in the tiny and decentralised sector, village and cottage`
  line `industries or of those engaged in the field of handicrafts" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 48 of 2003, s. 2, for "to any State co-operative bank" (w.e.f. 19-9-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (28765)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Conversion loan for production credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for section 22 (w.e.f. 19-9-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28765&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Conversion loan for production credit.-- Where the National Bank is satisfied that owing to`
  line `drought, famine or other natural calamities, military operations or enemy action, any State co-operative`
  line `bank, central co-operative bank, regional rural bank or any such financial institution or any financial`
  line `institution falling under any such class of financial institutions, as may be approved by the Reserve Bank`
  line `in this behalf, requires assistance under this section, it may provide to such bank or institution such`
  line `financial assistance as it may deem fit by way of making loans and advances repayable on the expiry of`
  line `fixed periods not exceeding seven years and on such terms and conditions as may be specified in this`
  line `behalf by the National Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that loans and advances may be made under this section only for the purpose of enabling the`
  line `borrowing bank or institution,--`
  line
  line `(a) to pay any dues to the National Bank for credit extended for financing agricultural operations`
  line `or the marketing of crops under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 21, or`
  line
  line `(b) (i) to make loans or advances to central co-operative banks or primary rural credit societies in`
  line `cases where the borrowing bank is a State co-operative bank, and`
  line
  line `(ii) to make loans and advances to primary rural credit societies in cases where the borrowing`
  line `bank is a central co-operative bank,`
  line
  line `and such loans or advances in both the cases being repayable on the expiry of fixed periods not being less`
  line `than eighteen months and not exceeding seven years, by way of reimbursement of loans and advances`
  line `made by such co-operative banks or societies for agriculture or agricultural operations or for`
  line `reimbursement of such loans or advances which have been converted into loans or advances repayable on`
  line `expiry of fixed periods not being less than eighteen months and not exceeding seven years from the date`
  line `of conversion:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no loan or advance shall be made under this section to a State co-operative bank`
  line `or a central co-operative bank unless such loan or advance is fully guaranteed as to the repayment of the`
  line `principal and payment of interest, by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (28766)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Rescheduling of loans to artisans, small-scale industries, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28766&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where the National Bank is`
  line `satisfied that owing to unforeseen circumstances the rescheduling of any loans and advances made to`
  line `artisans, ^1[village and cottage industries, micro enterprises, small enterprises and medium enterprises and`
  line `those engaged in the field of handicrafts, handlooms and other rural crafts], by any State co-operative`
  line `bank, regional rural bank or any such financial institution or any financial institution falling under such`
  line `class of financial institutions as may be approved by the Reserve Bank in this behalf, has become`
  line `necessary, it may provide to such bank or institution such financial assistance as it may deem fit by way`
  line `of loans and advances repayable on the expiry of fixed periods not being less than eighteen months and`
  line `not exceeding seven years against such securities as may be specified in this behalf by the National Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that no loan or advance shall be made under this section to a State co-operative bank unless`
  line `such loan or advance is fully guaranteed as to the repayment of the principal and payment of interest, by`
  line `the State Government but such guarantee may be waived by the National Bank if other security to the`
  line `satisfaction of the National Bank is furnished, or if, for reasons to be recorded by it in writing, the`
  line `National Bank is satisfied that the guarantee or other security is not necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 9, for "small-scale industries, industries in the tiny and decentralised sector, village and cottage`
  line `industries and those engaged in the field of handicrafts and other rural crafts," (w.e.f 15-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (28767)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Investment credit--medium term.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28767&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank shall provide such financial assistance`
  line `as it may consider necessary by way of making to State co-operative banks, regional rural banks, loans`
  line `and advances repayable on the expiry of fixed periods not being less than eighteen months and not`
  line `exceeding seven years against such securities as may be specified, in this behalf, by the National Bank`
  line `and such loans or advances may be made for agriculture, rural development or such other purposes as the`
  line `National Bank may, from time to time, determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that no loan or advance shall be made under this section to a State co-operative bank unless`
  line `such loan or advance is fully guaranteed as to the repayment of the principal and payment of interest, by`
  line `the State Government but such guarantee may be waived by the National Bank, if other security to the`
  line `satisfaction of the National Bank is furnished, or if, for reasons to be recorded by it in writing, the`
  line `National Bank is satisfied that the guarantee or other security is not necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (28768)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Other investment credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28768&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Bank may provide such financial assistance as it`
  line `may consider necessary for promoting agriculture and rural development by--`
  line
  line `(a) making loans and advances, by way of refinance, on such terms and conditions as the National`
  line `Bank may think fit to impose, to a State land development bank or a State co-operative bank or a`
  line `scheduled bank or any other financial institution approved by the Reserve Bank in this behalf, and`
  line `also rescheduling the payment of such loans and advances:`
  line
  line `Provided that the maximum period for which any such loan or advance may be granted, whether`
  line `originally or by rescheduling the payment thereof, shall not exceed twenty-five years;`
  line
  line `(b) purchasing or selling, or subscribing to the bonds or debentures issued by any bank or`
  line `institution referred to in clause (a) and repayable within a period not exceeding twenty-five years`
  line `from the dates on which they are issued;`
  line
  line `(c) making loans and advances on such terms and conditions as the National Bank may think fit`
  line `to impose, to a State co-operative bank or a scheduled bank for the purpose of enabling such bank to`
  line `make loans or advances to artisans, ^1[village and cottage industries, micro-enterprises, small`
  line `enterprises and medium enterprises and those engaged in the field of handicrafts, handlooms] and`
  line `other rural crafts and also rescheduling the payment of such loans and advances:`
  line
  line `Provided that the maximum period for which any such loan or advance may be granted, whether`
  line `originally or by rescheduling the payment thereof, shall not exceed twenty-five years;`
  line
  line `(d) making, where it is considered necessary so to do in connection with any financial assistance`
  line `under clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) to a State land development bank or a State co-operative`
  line `bank or a scheduled bank, loans and advances repayable on demand or on the expiry of a fixed period`
  line `not exceeding eighteen months, by way of refinance ^2[or otherwise] to such bank and also`
  line `rescheduling the payment of such loans and advances for such period as the National Bank may deem`
  line fit.
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, the provisions of`
  line `section 21 and section 24.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 10, for "small-scale industries, industries in the tiny and decentralised sector, village and cottage`
  line `industries and those engaged in the field of handicrafts" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (28769)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Purchase and sale of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28769&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Purchase and sale of shares.-- The National Bank may subscribe to, or purchase or sell stocks,`
  line `shares, bonds or debentures of, or invest in the securities of, any institution or class of institutions`
  line `concerned with agriculture and rural development which the Board may approve subject to such terms`
  line `and conditions as it may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (28770)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Loans to State Governments for share capital contribution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28770&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank may make`
  line `loans and advances to State Governments, repayable on the expiry of fixed periods not exceeding twenty`
  line `years from the date of making such loans and advances, from the National Rural Credit (Long Term`
  line `Operations) Fund established under section 42 for enabling them to subscribe directly or indirectly to the`
  line `share capital of a co-operative credit society.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (28771)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 28
  title `Loans to State Government, undertakings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28771&sectionno=27A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Loans to State Government, undertakings, etc.-- The National Bank may make loans and`
  line `advances to any State Government or a corporation owned or controlled by the State Government or to`
  line `any other person or class of persons, as may be approved by the Board, repayable on the expiry of a fixed`
  line `period not exceeding twenty-five years from the date of making of such loans and advances and subject to`
  line `such terms and conditions, as may be approved by the Board, for the purpose of development of`
  line `infrastructure facilities for promotion of agriculture and rural development.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (28772)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Security for credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28772&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) No accommodation shall be granted by the National Bank under`
  line `clause (a) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 25 or section 30 or section 32 to any institution other`
  line `than a scheduled bank unless it is fully and unconditionally guaranteed by the Government as to the`
  line `repayment of principal and payment of interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such guarantee shall be required in cases in which security to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Board is furnished by the borrowing institution.`
  line
  line `(2) No accommodation shall be granted by the National Bank under clause (a) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25 or section 32 to any scheduled bank unless security to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Board is furnished by such scheduled bank.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), no guarantee or`
  line `security referred to therein shall be required in cases in which the Board, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, decides that no such security or guarantee is necessary in respect of a scheduled bank, a State cooperative`
  line `bank or any person or class of persons, specifically approved by the Board or in respect of any`
  line `scheme or class of schemes, having regard to the nature and scope of the scheme or schemes for which`
  line `accommodation is proposed to be granted by the National Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (28773)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Amounts and securities to be held in trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28773&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any sums received by a borrowing institution`
  line `in repayment or realisation of loans and advances refinanced either wholly or partly by the National Bank shall, to the extent of the accommodation granted by the National Bank and remaining outstanding, be`
  line `deemed to have been received by the borrowing institution in trust for the National Bank, and shall`
  line `accordingly be paid by such institution to the National Bank, as per the repayment schedule fixed by the`
  line `National Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an accommodation has been granted to a borrowing institution, all securities held, or which`
  line `may be held, by such borrowing institution, on account of any transaction in respect of which such`
  line `accommodation has been granted by the National Bank, shall be held by such institution in trust for the`
  line `National Bank.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law for the time being in force, where`
  line `a liquidator is appointed for winding up a borrowing institution, it shall be the duty of the liquidator to`
  line `forthwith pass on to the National Bank the sums recovered by the borrowing institution or the liquidator,`
  line `as the case may be, in repayment or realisation of the loans and advances refinanced either wholly or`
  line `partly by the National Bank to the extent the refinance is outstanding and the National Bank shall be`
  line `entitled to enforce the securities held by the borrowing institution in trust for the National Bank as if`
  line `every reference to the borrowing institution in any contract, security or other document obtained by`
  line `borrowing institution is a reference to the National Bank and accordingly, the National Bank shall be`
  line `entitled to recover the balance sums due under such loans and advances from the constituents of`
  line `borrowing institution and any discharge given by the National Bank to such constituent shall be a valid`
  line `discharge and the liquidator shall, on demand made by the National Bank, deliver to it all such contracts,`
  line `securities and other documents, for due enforcement thereof by the National Bank.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the word "liquidator" shall include liquidator or a`
  line `provisional liquidator or any person or authority entrusted with the duty of liquidating the borrowing`
  line institution.]
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (28774)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Direct loans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 30 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28774&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Direct loans.-- The National Bank may, in exceptional circumstances to be recorded in writing`
  line `by the Board, by itself or in association with other financial institutions or scheduled banks, make loans`
  line `and advances, otherwise than by way of refinance to any person or class of persons or body corporate, on`
  line `such terms and conditions, including security and repayable within such period not exceeding twenty-five`
  line `years, as the National Bank may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (28775)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 32
  title `Bills rediscounting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 30 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28775&sectionno=30A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `[30A. Bills rediscounting.--The National Bank may rediscount bills of exchange and promissory`
  line `notes made, drawn, accepted or endorsed by any company or body corporate concerned with agriculture`
  line `and rural development presented by a scheduled bank, a State co-operative bank, State land development`
  line `bank, regional rural bank or any other institution or class of institutions approved by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (28776)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title Commission.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28776&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank may receive, for the rendering of any of the services`
  line `mentioned in this Chapter or Chapter VII, such commission or other consideration as may be agreed`
  line upon.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (28777)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Issue of guarantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for section 32 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28777&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[32. Issue of guarantees.-- The National Bank may guarantee, subject to such directions as may be`
  line `issued by the Board, from time to time, deferred payments in connection with the purchase of capital`
  line `goods or for any other purpose for giving effect to the provisions of this Act, due from any person or class`
  line `of persons, whether incorporated or not.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (28778)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to impose conditions for accommodation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "under this Chapter with a borrowing institution" (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28778&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `In entering into any transaction ^1[under this`
  line `Act with a borrower], the National Bank may impose such conditions as it may think necessary or`
  line `expedient for protecting the interests of the National Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (28779)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to call for repayment before agreed period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for section 34 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28779&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Power to call for repayment before agreed period.-- Notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in any agreement or arrangement, the National Bank may, by notice in writing, require`
  line `any borrower or assisted person to whom it has granted any loan or other financial assistance including grants, to discharge forthwith in full, the loan or other financial assistance, including grants, as the case`
  line `may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the National Bank that false or misleading information in any material`
  line `particulars was given in the application for the loan or other financial assistance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the borrower or the person has failed to comply with any of the terms of the contract or`
  line `arrangement with the National Bank in the matter of loan or other financial assistance, including`
  line `grants; or`
  line
  line `(c) if there is a reasonable apprehension that the borrower is unable to pay its debts or that`
  line `proceedings for liquidation may be commenced in respect thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) if for any reason it is necessary so to do, to protect the interests of the National Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (28780)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `National Bank to have access to records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 21, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28780&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The National Bank shall have free access to all`
  line `such records of a borrower seeking to avail of any credit or other facilities from the National Bank under`
  line `this Act and also to all such records of any person seeking to avail of any credit or other facilities from`
  line `such borrower, perusal whereof may appear to the National Bank to be necessary in connection with the`
  line `providing of finance or other assistance to such borrower or the refinancing of any loan or advance made`
  line `to such person by the borrower.]`
  line
  line `(2) The National Bank may require any institution or person referred to in sub-section (1) to furnish to`
  line `it copies of any of the records referred to in that sub-section and the institution or the person, as the case`
  line `may be, shall be bound to comply with such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (28781)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Validity of loan or advance not to be questioned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28781&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, the validity of any loan or advance granted by the`
  line `National Bank in pursuance of the provisions of this Act shall not be called in question merely on the`
  line `ground of non-compliance with the requirements of such other law as aforesaid or of any resolution,`
  line `contract, memorandum, articles of association or other instrument:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall render valid any loan or advance obtained by any company`
  line `or co-operative society where such company or co-operative society is not empowered by its`
  line `memorandum to obtain loans or advances.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (28782)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `National Bank not to grant loans or advances against its own bonds or debentures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28782&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line The
  line `National Bank shall not grant any loan or advance on the security of its own bonds or debentures.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (28783)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 40
  title `Prohibited business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28783&sectionno=37A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[37A. Prohibited business.-- (1) The National Bank shall not make any loans or advances under`
  line `section 30 or make any grants under this Act to any person or body of persons of which any of the`
  line `directors of the National Bank is a proprietor, partner, director, manager, agent, employee or guarantor or`
  line `in which one or more directors of the National Bank together hold substantial interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply to any borrower if any director of the National Bank--`
  line
  line `(a) is nominated as director of the Board of such borrower by the Government or a Government`
  line `company as defined ^2[in clause (45) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] or by a`
  line `corporation established by any other law;`
  line
  line `(b) is elected on the Board of such borrower by virtue of shares held in the borrower organisation`
  line `by the Government, or a Government company as defined ^2[in clause (45) of section 2 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) ] or by a corporation established by any other law,`
  line
  line `by reason only of such nomination or election, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "substantial interest", in relation to a borrower,`
  line `means the beneficial interest held by one or more of the directors of the National Bank or by any relative`
  line `of such director as defined ^3[in clause (77) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] whether`
  line `singly or taken together, in the shares of the borrower, the aggregate amount paid-up on which either`
  line `exceeds five lakhs of rupees or five per cent. of the paid-up share capital of the borrower, whichever is`
  line lesser.
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not apply to any borrower, if the National Bank is satisfied that it is necessary in the`
  line `public interest to enter into business with that borrower and entering into any kind of business with`
  line `such borrower shall be in accordance with and subject to such conditions and limitations, as may be`
  line `approved by the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) shall not apply to any transaction relating to the business entered into prior to the`
  line `commencement of the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2000 (55 of 2000), and all such business and any transaction in relation thereto may be`
  line `implemented or continued as if that Act had not come into force;`
  line
  line `(c) shall apply only so long as the conditions precedent to such disability as set out in the said`
  line `sub-section continue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 11, for "in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "in clause (41) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (28784)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 41
  title `Other functions of National Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28784&sectionno=38&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank--`
  line
  line `(i) shall co-ordinate its operations and the operations of various institutions engaged in the field`
  line `of rural credit and maintain expert staff to study all problems relating to agriculture and rural`
  line `development and be available for consultation to the Central Government, the Reserve Bank, the`
  line `State Governments and the other institutions engaged in the field of rural development;`
  line
  line `(ii) may act as the agent for the Central Government or a State Government or the Reserve Bank`
  line `in the transaction of any business in respect of loans and advances granted or to be granted, or bonds`
  line `or debentures purchased or subscribed for, or to be purchased or subscribed for;`
  line
  line `(iii) may provide facilities for training, for dissemination of information and the promotion of`
  line `research including the undertaking of studies, researches, techno-economic and other surveys in the`
  line `field of rural banking, agriculture and rural development and it may for the said purposes ^1[make`
  line `loans or advances or grants] including grants by way of provision for fellowships and chairs to any`
  line institution.
  line
  line `^2[(iv) may provide technical, legal, financial, marketing and administrative assistance to any`
  line `person engaged in agriculture and rural development activities;`
  line
  line `(v) may provide consultancy services in the field of agriculture and rural development and other`
  line `related matters in or outside India, on such terms and against such remuneration, as may be agreed`
  line upon;
  line
  line `(vi) may perform the functions entrusted to or required of the National Bank by any other law for`
  line `the time being in force; and`
  line
  line `(vii) do any other kind of business or undertake any other kind of activity which the Central`
  line `Government or the Reserve Bank may authorise.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 23, for "make grants" (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (28785)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 42
  title `Promotion of subsidiaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28785&sectionno=38A&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Promotion of subsidiaries.-- The National Bank may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank,`
  line `promote, form or manage or associate itself in promotion, formation or management of companies,`
  line `subsidiaries, affiliates, societies, trusts or such other association of persons, as it may deem fit, for the`
  line `purpose of carrying out its functions under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_b:
  sectionId (28786)
  sectionNo 38B
  orderNo 43
  title `Securitisation of debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28786&sectionno=38B&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[38B. Securitisation of debt.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the National Bank`
  line may--
  line
  line `(a) create one or more trusts and transfer loans and advances granted by it, with or without the`
  line `securities, to such trusts, for consideration;`
  line
  line `(b) set aside loans or advances held by the National Bank and issue and sell securities based upon`
  line `such loans or advances so set aside in the form of debt obligations, trust certificates of beneficial`
  line `interest or other instruments, by whatever name called, and act as a trustee for the holders of such`
  line securities.]
obj_root_law_sections_38_c:
  sectionId (28787)
  sectionNo 38C
  orderNo 44
  title `Exemption from compulsory registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28787&sectionno=38C&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_38_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[38C.Exemption from compulsory registration.--Notwithstanding anything contained in subsection`
  line `(1) of section 17 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908)--`
  line
  line `(a) any instrument in the form of debt obligations or trust certificate of beneficial interest or any`
  line `other instrument, by whatsoever name called, issued by the National Bank or the trust created by it to`
  line `securitise the loans granted by it and not creating, declaring, assigning, limiting or extinguishing any`
  line `right, title or interest to or in immovable property; or`
  line
  line `(b) any transfer of such instruments referred to in clause (a), shall not require compulsory`
  line registration.]
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (28788)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 45
  title `Incidental powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28788&sectionno=39&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank may also do all such things as may be necessary or`
  line `incidental to or consequential upon the exercise of its powers, discharge of its functions and the`
  line `performance of its duties, under this Act, or under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (28789)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 46
  title `Deposits and investments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for section 40 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28789&sectionno=40&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^1[40. Deposits and investments.--(1) The National Bank may invest its funds in promissory notes,`
  line `stocks or securities of the Central Government or keep the moneys deposited with the Reserve Bank or`
  line `with any agency of the Reserve Bank or with a State co-operative bank or a scheduled bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or section 30A, the National Bank may, for`
  line `beneficial investment of its surplus funds, rediscount bills of exchange or promissory notes arising out of`
  line `bona fide trade and commercial transactions and also lend repayable at call or short notice to a scheduled`
  line `bank or any financial institution approved by the Reserve Bank, or invest in certificates of deposit and`
  line `other instruments or schemes as may be approved by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (28790)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 47
  title `Credit information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28790&sectionno=41&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank may, for the purpose of the efficient discharge of its`
  line `functions under this Act, collect from or furnish to the Central Government, the Reserve Bank or any`
  line `banking company or such other financial institution as may be notified by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, credit information or other information.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expressions "banking company" and "credit`
  line `information" shall have the same meanings as in section 45A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934`
  line `(2 of 1934).`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (28791)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 48
  title `National Rural Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28791&sectionno=42&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Bank shall establish`
  line `and maintain a Fund to be known as the National Rural Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall (in addition to assets and liabilities transferred under section 18) include,--`
  line
  line `(a) such sums of money as the Central Government and the State Governments may contribute`
  line `from time to time;`
  line
  line `(b) such sums of money as the Reserve Bank may contribute every year; and`
  line
  line `(c) such further sums of money as the Board may contribute every year.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount in the said Fund shall be applied by the National Bank only to provide financial`
  line `assistance by way of loans and advances under section 23, section 24, sub-section (1) of section 25 or`
  line `section 27 or for the purposes of section 26.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (28792)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 49
  title `National Rural Credit (Stabilisation) Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28792&sectionno=43&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Bank shall establish and`
  line `maintain a Fund to be known as the National Rural Credit (Stabilisation) Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall (in addition to assets and liabilities transferred under section 18) include,--`
  line
  line `(a) such sums of money as the Central Government and the State Governments may contribute`
  line `from time to time;`
  line
  line `(b) such sums of money as the Reserve Bank may contribute every year; and`
  line
  line `(c) such further sums of money as the Board may contribute every year.`
  line
  line `(3) The amounts in the said Fund shall be applied by the National Bank only to provide loans and`
  line `advances under section 22.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (28793)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 50
  title `Research and Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 26, for "making of grants" (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28793&sectionno=44&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Bank shall establish and maintain a Fund`
  line `to be known as the Research and Development Fund, to which shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) such sums of money as are transferable to this Fund in accordance with section 47;`
  line
  line `(b) such sums of money as the Board may contribute every year to this Fund from out of its`
  line `annual profits; and`
  line
  line `(c) such gifts, grants, donations or benefactions which the National Bank may receive and which`
  line `the Board may earmark for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The Research and Development Fund shall be expended on matters of importance to agriculture,`
  line `agricultural operations and rural development, including the provision of training and research facilities`
  line `and the ^1[making of loans or advances or grants] under clause (iii) of section 38.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (28794)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 51
  title `Reserve Fund and other Funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for "and such other Funds" (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28794&sectionno=45&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank shall establish a Reserve Fund ^1[and other`
  line `Funds] as the Board may consider necessary by transferring such sums as it may deem fit, out of its`
  line `annual profits and out of receipts from gifts, grants, donations or benefactions, which it may receive.`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (28795)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 52
  title `Preparation of balance-sheet, etc., of National Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28795&sectionno=46&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The balance-sheet and accounts of`
  line `the National Bank shall be prepared and maintained in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the National Bank to be balanced and closed as`
  line `on the thirtieth day of June ^1[or such other date in each year as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify].`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that with a view to facilitating the transition from one period of accounting to another`
  line `period of accounting under this sub-section, the Central Government may, by order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make such provisions as it considers necessary or expedient for the balancing and`
  line `closing of, or for other matters relating to, the books or accounts in respect of the concerned years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 46, for ", each year" (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 46, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (28796)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 53
  title `Disposal of surplus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 28, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28796&sectionno=47&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `After making provision for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation of assets`
  line `and all other matters for which provision is necessary or expedient or which is usually provided for by`
  line `bankers, and for the Funds referred to in sections 42, 43 and 45, the National Bank shall transfer--`
  line
  line `(i) for a period of fifteen years, following the accounting year during which the National Bank is`
  line `established, the amount remaining (hereafter in this section referred to as surplus) to the Research and`
  line `Development Fund under section 44; and`
  line
  line `^1[(ii) after the expiry of the said period of fifteen years, the Board shall, after making provision`
  line `for the Fund referred to in clause (i), disburse or spend the balance of the surplus in such manner as`
  line `may be approved by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (28797)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 54
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 12, for "section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)"(w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28797&sectionno=48&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of the National Bank shall be audited by auditors duly qualified to act`
  line `as auditors under sub-section (1) of ^1[section 141 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] who shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government in consultation with the Reserve Bank, for such term and on such`
  line `remuneration as the Central Government may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditors shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance-sheet of the National Bank and it`
  line `shall be their duty to examine it together with the accounts and vouchers relating thereto and they shall`
  line `have a list delivered to them of all books kept by the National Bank and shall at all reasonable times have`
  line `access to the books, accounts, vouchers and other documents of the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditors may, in relation to the accounts of the National Bank, examine any director of the`
  line `Board or any officer or other employee of the National Bank and shall be entitled to require from the`
  line `Board or officers or employees of the National Bank such information and explanation as they may think`
  line `necessary for the performance of their duties.`
  line
  line `(4) The auditors shall make a report to the National Bank upon the annual balance-sheet and accounts`
  line `examined by them and in every such report, they shall state whether in their opinion the balance-sheet is a`
  line `full and fair balance-sheet containing all necessary particulars and properly drawn up so as to exhibit a`
  line `true and fair view of the state of affairs of the National Bank and in case they had called for any`
  line `explanation or information from the Board or any officer or other employee of the National Bank,`
  line `whether it has been given and whether it is satisfactory.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Bank shall furnish to the Central Government and the Reserve Bank within four`
  line `months from the date on which the annual accounts of the National Bank are closed and balanced, a copy`
  line `of its balance-sheet as on the close of that year together with a copy of the profit and loss account for the`
  line `year and a copy of the auditors report and a report of the working of the National Bank during the`
  line `relevant year, and the Central Government shall, as soon as may be after they are received by it, cause the`
  line `same to be laid before each House of Parliament and cause the copies of the said balance-sheet, profit and`
  line `loss account and auditors' report to be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to anything contained in the preceding sub-sections, the Central Government`
  line `may, at any time, appoint the Comptroller and Auditor General of India to examine and report upon the`
  line `accounts of the National Bank and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such examination`
  line `and report shall be payable by the National Bank to the Comptroller and Auditor General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (28798)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 55
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28798&sectionno=49&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The National Bank shall furnish, from time to time, to the Central Government and to`
  line `the Reserve Bank, such returns as the Central Government or the Reserve Bank may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (28799)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 56
  title `Staff of National Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28799&sectionno=50&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Bank may appoint such number of officers and other`
  line `employees as it considers necessary or desirable for the efficient performance of its functions and`
  line `determine the terms and conditions of their appointment and service.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the National Bank to`
  line `utilise, and for the Reserve Bank to make available, the services of such staff of the Reserve Bank on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be agreed upon between the National Bank and the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (6), at any time before the expiry of six months from the`
  line `appointed day, the Reserve Bank may, in public interest, transfer to the National Bank, such members of`
  line `the staff of Reserve Bank whom the Reserve Bank considers as engaged, or as suitable to be engaged, in`
  line `attending to the work of a nature which is same or similar to that which the National Bank may require for`
  line `its efficient functioning, and upon such transfer they shall be deemed to be appointed by the National`
  line `Bank under sub-section (1) with effect from the date of such transfer:`
  line
  line `Provided that every person so transferred may, before the expiry of a period of six months from the`
  line `appointed day, or before the expiry of a period of thirty days from such transfer, whichever period expires`
  line `later, elect to go back to the Reserve Bank by exercising an option in writing to that effect, the option`
  line `once exercised being final, and on the exercise of such option, the Reserve Bank shall, before the expiration of a period of eighteen months from the appointed day, take back such member of the staff and`
  line `he shall be deemed to have been on deputation to the National Bank during the period he was a member`
  line `of the staff of the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) Any member of the staff of the Reserve Bank who is not appointed under sub-section (3), may,`
  line `if he so desires, make an application to the Reserve Bank within six months from the appointed day, to be`
  line `considered for appointment as a member of the staff of the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(b) The Reserve Bank may, in consultation with the National Bank, consider such application having`
  line `regard to the suitability of the person so applying, the availability of vacancies in the National Bank, the`
  line `exigencies of service in the Reserve Bank and the National Bank and such other factors as may be`
  line `considered relevant in this regard, and, if the Reserve Bank is satisfied having regard to these factors, that`
  line `such applicant is suitable for being so appointed recommend his appointment to the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(c) The National Bank may thereupon, within eighteen months from the appointed day, appoint such a`
  line `person applying under this sub-section, as a member of the staff of the National Bank, and on such`
  line `appointment, such a person shall be deemed to have been appointed in the National Bank under`
  line `sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided that the proviso to sub-section (3) and the proviso to sub-section (5) shall not apply in`
  line `respect of such a person.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this Act or in any other law or in any contract,`
  line `for the time being in force, at any time before the expiry of six months from the appointed day, the`
  line `Reserve Bank may, if it considers it necessary in consultation with the National Bank so to do in the`
  line `interest of the National Bank, transfer on promotion any member of the staff of the National Bank to the`
  line `Reserve Bank, and on such transfer to the Reserve Bank, each such member of the staff shall be deemed`
  line `to be a member of the staff of the Reserve Bank and shall be entitled to the same salary, emoluments and`
  line `other conditions of service to which he was entitled immediately before the date of such transfer,`
  line `including benefits, if any, arising directly out of such promotion:`
  line
  line `Provided that every member of the staff who is transferred as aforesaid may, before the expiry of a`
  line `period of six months from the appointed day or within thirty days from such transfer, whichever period`
  line `expires later, elect to go back to the National Bank by exercising an option in writing to that effect, the`
  line `option once exercised being final, and on the exercise of such option, the National Bank shall, before the`
  line `expiration of a period of eighteen months from the appointed day, take back such member of the staff and`
  line `he shall be deemed to have been on deputation to the Reserve Bank during the period he was a member of`
  line `the staff of the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(6) Every person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who, immediately before the date appointed under sub-section (1) of section 16, is a member`
  line `of the staff of the Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(b) who is a member of the staff of the Reserve Bank but whose services are being utilised`
  line `immediately before that date by the said Corporation,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be appointed by the National Bank under sub-section (1) on the said date:`
  line
  line `Provided that every member of the staff of the Reserve Bank, who is so deemed to be appointed, and`
  line `who was not recruited specifically for utilisation in the Agricultural Refinance and Development`
  line `Corporation, may, before the expiry of a period of six months from the appointed day or within a period`
  line `of thirty days from the date appointed under sub-section (1) of section 16, whichever period expires later,`
  line `elect to go back to the Reserve Bank by exercising an option in writing to that effect, the option once`
  line `exercised being final, and on the exercise of such option, the Reserve Bank shall, before the expiration of`
  line `a period of eighteen months from the appointed day, take back such member of the staff and he shall be`
  line `deemed to have been on deputation to the National Bank during the period he was a member of the staff`
  line `of the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law or in any agreement, for the time being in`
  line `force, no member of the staff shall be entitled to claim any compensation for, or in relation to any matter concerning, his transfer, appointment or as the case may be, return, under sub-sections (3) to (6) and no`
  line `claim in respect thereof shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (10) and sub-section (11), every member of the staff of`
  line `the Agricultural Refinance and Development Corporation or of the Reserve Bank who is deemed to be`
  line `appointed as a member of the staff of the National Bank under this section, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `appointed by the National Bank on the same salary, emoluments and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `to which he was entitled immediately before his appointment in the National Bank.`
  line
  line `(9) The provisions relating to superannuation benefits, namely, the regulations relating to provident`
  line `fund and the rules relating to payment of gratuity and compassionate gratuity and any other provision`
  line `relating to superannuation as are applicable to the staff of the Reserve Bank on the appointed day shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply to the staff of the National Bank, unless and until the National Bank alters or amends`
  line `the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that after the appointed day, any such alteration or amendment may be effected by the`
  line `National Bank as regards provident fund regulations in accordance with section 60, and as regards the`
  line `other rules in the manner they would have been altered or amended but for this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that after the expiry of six months from the appointed day, the balances held in the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Employees Provident Fund to the credit of any member of the staff of the Reserve`
  line `Bank whose services are transferred under this section to the National Bank and who does not opt to go`
  line `back to the Reserve Bank, shall be transferred to, and held in, the Provident Fund of the National Bank on`
  line `same or similar terms subject to which those balances were held earlier in the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Employees Provident Fund.`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, settlement, or agreement, every person`
  line `employed by the National Bank or whose services have been transferred to the National Bank under this`
  line `Act, shall be liable to serve anywhere in India.`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, or in any award, judgment, decree, decision or order of any`
  line `Industrial Tribunal, Court or other authority, or any settlement or agreement, made or entered into before`
  line `the date of transfer to the National Bank of the services of any person under this section, the National`
  line `Bank shall be free to alter, amend or repeal in such manner and to such extent it may consider necessary,`
  line `any of the terms and conditions of service applicable to such persons whose services are so transferred to`
  line `the National Bank and who are appointed in the National Bank under this section except that the National`
  line `Bank shall not alter to their prejudice the terms relating to payment of salary and other emoluments,`
  line `retirement benefits and eligibility for leave.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "appointed day" means the date of establishment of`
  line `the National Bank under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (28800)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 57
  title `Obligation as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 14-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28800&sectionno=51&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Bank shall not, except as otherwise`
  line `required by this Act or any other law, divulge any information relating to, or to the affairs of, its`
  line `constituents except in circumstances in which it is, in accordance with the law or practice and usage`
  line `customary among bankers, necessary or appropriate for the National Bank to divulge such information.`
  line
  line `(2) Every director, member of a committee, auditor, officer or other employee of the National Bank or`
  line `of the Reserve Bank, whose services are utilised by the National Bank under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in the form set out in the`
  line `First Schedule to this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005 (30 of 2005).]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (28801)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 58
  title `Defects in appointment not to invalidate acts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28801&sectionno=52&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or proceeding of the Board or of`
  line `any committee of the National Bank shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board or the committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) No act done by any person acting in good faith as a director of the Board or as a member of a`
  line `committee of the National Bank shall become invalid merely on the ground that he was disqualified to be`
  line `a director or that there was any other defect in his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52_a:
  sectionId (28802)
  sectionNo 52A
  orderNo 59
  title `Agreement with National Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28802&sectionno=52A&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[52A. Agreement with National Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.--(1) Where any`
  line `agreement entered into by the National Bank with a company or a body corporate while granting loans`
  line `and advances, provides for the appointment by the National Bank of one or more directors of such`
  line `company or body corporate, such provisions and any appointment of directors made in pursuance thereof`
  line `shall be valid and effective, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in ^2[the Companies Act,`
  line `2013 (18 of 2013)] or in any other law for the time being in force, or in the memorandum, articles of`
  line `association or any other instrument relating to the company or body corporate, and any provision`
  line `regarding share qualification, age-limit, number of directorships, removal from office of directors and`
  line `such like conditions contained in any such law or instrument aforesaid, shall not apply to any director`
  line `appointed by the National Bank in pursuance of the agreement as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Any director appointed as aforesaid shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the National Bank and may be removed or substituted by`
  line `any person by order in writing of the National Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director or for anything done`
  line `or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in relation`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2018, s. 13, for "the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 15-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (28803)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 60
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28803&sectionno=53&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the National Bank or any director or any officer or other employee of the National Bank or any other`
  line `person authorised by the National Bank to discharge any functions under this Act for any loss or damage`
  line `caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act or of any other law or provision having the force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (28804)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 61
  title `Indemnity of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28804&sectionno=54&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director shall be indemnified by the National Bank against`
  line `all losses and expenses incurred by him in, or in relation to, the discharge of his duties, except such as are`
  line `caused by his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A director shall not be responsible for any other director or for any officer or other employee of`
  line `the National Bank or for any loss or expenses resulting to the National Bank from the insufficiency or`
  line `deficiency of the value of, or title to, any property or security acquired or taken on behalf of the National`
  line `Bank or the insolvency or wrongful act of any debtor or any person under obligation to the National Bank`
  line `or anything done in good faith in the execution of the duties of his office in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (28805)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 62
  title [Omitted].
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28805&sectionno=55&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `[Exemption from income-tax, etc.]--Omitted by the Finance Act, 2001 (14 of 2001), s. 140 (w.e.f.`
  line `1-4-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (28806)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 63
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 22-01-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28806&sectionno=56&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever in any return, balance-sheet, or other document or in any information`
  line `required or furnished by or under or for the purposes of any provision of this Act, wilfully makes a`
  line `statement which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false, or wilfully omits to make a`
  line `material statement, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) If any person fails to produce any book, account or other document, or to furnish any statement or`
  line `information which, under the provisions of this Act, it is his duty to produce or furnish, he shall be liable to`
  line `penalty which may extend to one lakh fifty thousand rupees in respect of each failure and in the case of a`
  line `continuing failure, an additional penalty which may extend to seven thousand five hundred rupees for every`
  line `day during which the failure continues after the first such failure.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of adjudging penalty under sub-section (2), the National Bank shall serve notice on`
  line `the person`
  line `requiring it to show cause why the amount specified in the notice should not be imposed as a penalty and a`
  line reasonable
  line `opportunity of being heard shall also be given to such person.`
  line
  line `(4) Any penalty imposed by the National Bank under this section shall be payable within a period of`
  line `fourteen days from the date on which notice issued by the National Bank demanding payment of the sum is`
  line `served on the person and, in the event of failure of the person to pay the sum within such period, may be`
  line `levied on a direction made by the principal civil court having jurisdiction in the area where the person is`
  line `situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction shall be made except on an application made to the court by the`
  line `National Bank or by any officer authorised by the National Bank in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The court which makes a direction under sub-section (4) shall issue a certificate specifying the sum`
  line `payable by the person and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same manner as if it were a`
  line `decree made by the court in a civil suit.`
  line
  line `(6) No complaint shall be filed against any person in any court relating to any contravention or default in`
  line `respect of which any penalty has been imposed by the National Bank under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(7) Where any complaint has been filed against any person in any court in respect of the contravention`
  line `or default of the nature referred to in sub-section (1), then, no proceedings for the imposition of any penalty`
  line `on the person shall be initiated under sub-section (2).]`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (28807)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 64
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28807&sectionno=57&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence has been committed by a company, every person`
  line `who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to the company for the`
  line `conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (28808)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 65
  title `Bankers' Books Evidence Act, 1891, to apply in relation to National Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28808&sectionno=58&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The Bankers'`
  line `Books Evidence Act, 1891 (18 of 1891), shall apply in relation to the National Bank as if it were a bank`
  line `as defined in section 2 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (28809)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 66
  title `Liquidation of National Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28809&sectionno=59&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of companies`
  line `shall apply to the National Bank and the National Bank shall not be placed in liquidation save by order of`
  line `the Central Government and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (28810)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 67
  title `Power of Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872&sectionId=28810&sectionno=60&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00002_198161_1517807321872
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and in consultation with the Reserve Bank, by notification, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the`
  line `purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the fees or allowances that may be paid to the directors or members of the Advisory Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the times and places of the meetings of the Board or the Executive Committee or the Advisory`
  line `Council and the procedure to be followed at such meetings including the quorum necessary for the`
  line `transaction of business;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of directors constituting the Executive Committee and the functions that such`
  line `Committee shall discharge;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner and terms of issue and redemption of bonds and debentures by the National Bank;`
  line
  line `^1[(e) the manner of election of directors under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 6;]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(g) The form and manner in which the balance-sheets and the accounts of the National Bank shall`
  line `be prepared or maintained;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(i) the duties and conduct, salaries, allowances and conditions of service of officers and other`
  line employees;
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and maintenance of provident or other benefit funds for employees of the`
  line `National Bank; and`
  line
  line `(k) such other matters for which the Board may consider it expedient or necessary to provide for`
  line `by way of regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Any regulation which may be made by the Board under this Act may be made by the Reserve`
  line `Bank, in consultation with the Central Government, before the expiry of three months from the date of`
  line `establishment of the National Bank, and any regulation so made may be altered and rescinded by the`
  line `Board in the exercise of its powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The power to make regulations conferred by this section shall include the power to give`
  line `retrospective effect to the regulations or any of them from a date not earlier than the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, but no retrospective effect shall be given to any regulation so as to`
  line `prejudicially affect the interest of any person to whom such regulation may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall cause every regulation made under this Act to be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be`
  line `made, the regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 2000, s. 30, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Clauses (f) and (h) omitted by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2001).`
